  identifier: ReactiveEvent3
  type: 1
  question:
    sentences:
    - Your counsellor advised you to get a pet. She said it is trending between kings
      and nobles. Something about good impression and loyalty and stuff.
  answers:
  - identifier: 1
    answerText: A fox. You heard the alchemists said it guards a stone that gives
      immortality.
    statChanges:
    - socialClass: 4
      changeValue: 20
    rivalStatChanges: []
    popChanges:
    - socialClass: 4
      changeValue: 20
    resolution:
      sentences:
      - "<Player> adopted a fox. The cunning animal attracted the attention of the
        alchemists from other kingdoms, as well as from the ones in your own.\r"
  - identifier: 2
    answerText: You know, like they always say at church "the lamb of God". A lamb
      could make me blessed.
    statChanges:
    - socialClass: 5
      changeValue: 20
    rivalStatChanges: []
    popChanges:
    - socialClass: 5
      changeValue: 20
    resolution:
      sentences:
      - "<Player> adopted a lamb. The symbol of devotion was well-received by the
        church, and clergymen came to live in this kingdom with a such devoted heir.\r"
  - identifier: 3
    answerText: A rabbit. The merchants said it gives luck and riches. At least that's
      why it was expensive.
    statChanges:
    - socialClass: 0
      changeValue: 20
    rivalStatChanges: []
    popChanges:
    - socialClass: 0
      changeValue: 40
    resolution:
      sentences:
      - "<Player> adopted a rabbit. The fluffy and lucky little rodent gave hope to
        the merchants from your kingdom. It also made some merchants from other kingdoms
        seeking more luck to move in.\r"
  - identifier: 4
    answerText: Get a Lion. Nothing more befitting of a king as the king of animals.
    statChanges:
    - socialClass: 3
      changeValue: 20
    rivalStatChanges: []
    popChanges:
    - socialClass: 3
      changeValue: 40
    resolution:
      sentences:
      - '<Player> somehow adopted a lion. This true display of nobility and power
        put the nobles in awe. '
      - "Some nobles from other kingdoms even swore their fielty to you as new vassals.\r"
